sharapanjara ( kannada : ಶರಪಂಜರ ) ( english : cage of arrows ) is a 1971 indian kannada language film directed by puttanna kanagal , based on a novel by triveni of the same name , and starring kalpana and gangadhar in lead roles . this film is considered one of the best kannada movies ever made . the film won the award for best feature film in kannada at the 20th national film awards in 1972 . it also won three awards at the 1970-71 karnataka state film awards including the award for first best film . the film was later remade in telugu as krishnaveni ( 1974 ) starring vanisri .